Subject: [Linuxdcpp-developers] Download queue by TTH - not filename
Message-ID: <430c80e90712030215u5a2c83a5l4b8f35f087e53e74@mail.gmail.com>

Hello,
I've noticed that when two files with the same TTH but diff filenames
are clicked,
we get these two files with same TTH in the download queue.
This is a problem when we try to download a file from a user with
no slots. We then search for the file using "Search for alternates"
which searches
using TTH. This lists out files with same TTH and diff file names.
When we select a
file from this alternate list with a different filename, we should get
only one file in
the download queue.
I suggest we populate the download queue after searching the existing
queued files
and try to match the TTH. If we get a slot from other user, we first
remove the previous
file and then add this new file to the download queue.

Any suggestions?

Hope u understood this.

thanks,

Hello,

The gui code that treats urls or other tags in hub chat and PM windows does
not work properly. When moved over the active text (tag) the cursor either does
not change at all or changes in an unpredictable manner, or stays as hand after
a click and moving the pointer off the tag, etc.

between the original code of the magnet patch and Steven's code.

It was also clear that there was some duplication of code in hub.cc and
privatemessage.cc. I decided not to touch this and I simply edited the
code in both places.

The patch is attached.
